    {
      "title": "Out-of-View Scene Evolution",
      "description": "This section evaluates whether the model can infer scene dynamics beyond the initially observed egocentric view. Another person appears in the anchor view but is invisible from the egocentric perspective, becoming visible only after a viewpoint change by the first-person player. We alter the timing of the viewpoint transition by editing the egocentric human motion, such as deleting or duplicating a human pose segment, and examine whether the generated scene evolution remains temporally consistent. Human Action 1 and Result 1 form one paired result, while Human Action 2 and Result 2 form another.",
